<p>The <code>redirect</code> tag performs an HTTP redirect to another URL.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}redirect 'url'{close}</pre>

<h2>Basic Redirect</h2>
<pre>{open}redirect '?homepage'{close}</pre>
<p>Redirects to the homepage within the current app.</p>

<h2>External Redirect</h2>
<pre>{open}redirect 'https://example.com'{close}</pre>
<p>Redirects to an external URL.</p>

<h2>Conditional Redirect</h2>
<pre>{open}if $loggedIn eq FALSE{close}
  {open}redirect '?login'{close}
{open}/if{close}</pre>
<p>Redirect to login page if user is not logged in.</p>

<h2>Redirect After Action</h2>
<pre>{open}if $formSubmitted eq TRUE{close}
  // Process form...
  {open}redirect '?thankyou'{close}
{open}/if{close}</pre>
<p>Redirect to thank you page after form submission.</p>

<h2>Common Use Cases</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Post-form submission redirects</li>
  <li>Authentication flow redirects</li>
  <li>URL canonicalization</li>
  <li>Access control</li>
  <li>Page moved permanently</li>
</ul>

<h2>Warning</h2>
<p style="color:red">The redirect tag immediately stops page processing and sends an HTTP redirect header. Any content after the redirect tag will not be rendered.</p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>This demo page does not actually redirect. In real usage, the redirect happens immediately when the tag is processed.</p>
